article.headline: Florida A&M 72, South Carolina St 65
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Tony Tate scored 25 points as Florida A&M beat South Carolina State 72-65 Monday night. The game was close until the Rattlers (8-9, 4-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) went on a 13-2 run midway through the second half. The Bulldogs (4-11, 2-3) cut the lead to seven late but got no closer in their first home game of the season. Florida A&M made eight of its 13 3-ponters and shot 56 percent (28-of-50) from the field for the game. South Carolina State was 7-of-24 from behind the arc and shot 38.6 percent (22-of-57) from the field. Travis Jones and Brian Mason each scored 15 points, while Thurman Zimmerman added 13 points and six rebounds for the Bulldogs. Rome Sanders, Michael Sams and Glen Elliot each added 12 points for the Rattlers.
